  <summary>3/29/2001--Introduced.
Orphan Drug Tax Credit Act of 2001 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to move up the date for which a taxpayer may claim the credit for the clinical testing of drugs for rare diseases or conditions (orphan drugs) from the date a drug is designated an orphan drug to the date the application for such designation is filed.</summary>
